Ancient India (3300 BCE - 1200 CE):

* Indus Valley Civilization (3300-1300 BCE): This was the earliest known civilization in India, located in present-day Pakistan and northwestern India. It was known for its advanced urban planning, architecture, and water management systems.
* Vedic Period (1300-500 BCE): This period saw the composition of the Vedas, Hinduism's sacred texts, as well as the rise of the Brahmin caste.
* Mauryan Empire (322-185 BCE): The Mauryan Empire was established by Chandragupta Maurya and reached its peak during the reign of Ashoka the Great, who spread Buddhism throughout India and beyond.

Medieval India (1200-1756 CE):

* Islamic Invasions (1000-1526 CE): Muslim invaders from Central Asia began arriving in India around 1000 CE, eventually establishing the Delhi Sultanate in 1206 CE.
* Mughal Empire (1526-1756 CE): The Mughal Empire was founded by Babur in 1526 CE and reached its peak under Akbar the Great (1556-1605 CE), who promoted religious tolerance and artistic achievement.

Modern India (1756 CE - Present):

* British Colonization (1756-1947 CE): The British East India Company established itself in India through trade and political maneuvering, leading to the eventual colonization of the country.
* Indian Independence Movement (1857-1947 CE): This period saw various movements and reforms aimed at gaining independence from British colonial rule.
* Post-Independence India (1947 CE - Present): After gaining independence in 1947, India became a democratic republic with a federal government structure. Over the decades since, India has experienced rapid economic growth, social change, and political developments.

